    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flexible cords from lamps, usually coated with rubber. They generally run through the base of a lamp, and connect at the socket where the bulb is screwed in. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051994/Carter, Wiring 101 (2006)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>自電燈延伸出來、具有彈性的線，通常以絕緣橡膠包覆。一般從燈座底部延伸連接至旋裝燈泡的插座。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flexibles Kabel einer Lampe, im Allgemeinen ummantelt mit Gummi. Generell verläuft es durch den Fuß der Lampe und ist mit der Fassung verbunden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
